      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum solid mechanics with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity and frictional contact is an established model form for metallic implant compression-bending; documented precedent in peer-reviewed literature.",
      "rationale": "The continuum solid mechanics formulation with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity and augmented Lagrange frictional contact is well-established for titanium alloy implant structural analysis. Multiple peer-reviewed publications (including Nagaraja et al. 2022, doi:10.1115/1.4054413) confirm this model form is appropriate for ASTM F1717 compression-bending scenarios. Required level 3 achieved."
