      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading magnitudes and boundary conditions; at minimum two distinct load levels or construct configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single load level and construct configuration per ASTM F1717. While this fully characterises the standard test condition, it does not span multiple clinically relevant loading scenarios. Achieved level 2 (single condition, well-characterised) versus required level 3. This known gap is accepted given the regulatory precedent for F1717 as the standard acceptance test and the medium model risk level."
    },
