      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified in ASTM F1717 and are mechanistically linked to clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three primary QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 for pedicle screw construct acceptance. Each QoI is mechanistically linked to a clinical failure mode: stiffness to subsidence, yield force to permanent deformation, and force at 40 mm to catastrophic fracture. Required level 3 achieved."
