  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026-04-19",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/depuy-synthes-computational-mechanics",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required credibility level. The single exception (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent for ASTM F1717 as the standard acceptance protocol and the medium model risk classification. The overall evidence package is judged sufficient to support the claim that the FEA framework reliably predicts F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within the pre-established acceptance bounds. The ValidationResult was generated under model configuration ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7-rc2; the released model of record is ansys-mechanical-2026-q1-build-7. The configuration management team has documented that the sole difference between rc2 and the release build is a correction to the automated HTML report template, with no change to solver numerics, contact algorithms, or post-processing calculations. On this basis the credibility assessment team accepted the rc2 validation outputs as applicable to the released build without re-execution. Decision: Accepted.",
